Name: TypeOfSamplingInformationGroup
Description: A generic element for specifying a reason for a sampling information group. Note that this element can contain either a term from a controlled vocabulary list or a textual description.

Name: SamplingInformationGroupName
Description: A name for the sampling information group. May be expressed in multiple languages. Repeat the element to express names with different content, for example different names for different systems.

Name: Label
Description: A display label for the sampling information group. Supports multiple language versions of the same content as well as optional formatting of the content. Repeat for labels with different content, for example, labels with differing length limitations.

Name: Description
Description: Additional textual description of the sampling information group. Supports multiple language versions of the same content as well as optional formatting of the content.

Name: UniverseReference
Description: Reference to the universe statement describing the persons or other elements that the sampling information objects refer to, and to which any analytic results refer.

Name: ConceptReference
Description: Reference to the concept measured by the sampling information objects in this group.

Name: SampleFrameReference
Description: A sample frame item included in the scheme by reference.

Name: SamplingPlanReference
Description: A sampling plan item included in the scheme by reference.

Name: SampleReference
Description: A sample included in the scheme by reference.

Name: SamplingInformationGroupReference
Description: Inclusion of a SamplingInformationGroup by reference.

Name: IsOrdered
Description: Indicates that the content of the group is ordered.
